!!! 5
%html
  %head
    %meta{ :charset => "utf-8" }
    %meta{ :"http-equiv" => "X-UA-Compatible", :content => "IE=edge,chrome=1" }
    %meta{ :"http-equiv" => "Content-Type", :content => "text/html" }
    %meta{ :name => "viewport", :content => "width=device-width" }
    %title Droplings for Mac

    :javascript
      if ( top !== self ) { top.location = self.location.href; }

    %link{ :rel => "shortcut icon", :href => "img/favicon.png" }
    %link{ :rel => "stylesheet", :type => "text/css", :href => "css/foundation.css" }
    %link{ :rel => "stylesheet", :type => "text/css", :href => "css/droplings.css" }
    %link{ :rel => "stylesheet", :type => "text/css", :href => "http://assets.drpln.gs/1/font-awesome.css" }
    /[if IE 7 ]
      %link{ :rel => "stylesheet", :type => "text/css", :href => "http://assets.drpln.gs/1/font-awesome-ie7.css" }

    /[if lt IE 9]
      %script{ :src => "http://html5shiv.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/html5.js" }

  %body

    .row
      .seven.columns.centered
        #drop-img
          %img{ :src => "img/app-icon.png", :alt => "Droplings icon" }

        %p

        %h1
          %small This is
          Droplings for Mac.

        %p
          %img{ :src => "http://placehold.it/518x120", :title => "Screenshot" }

        %p
          It's a menubar icon.  If you drop a file on it, it'll build a nice
          %strong preview page
          around it, upload both to
          %strong your Dropbox,
          then copy the public preview link to your clipboard.

        %p<
          Droplings comes with a clean preview page theme (see the download
          link below for an example), but you can use
          %strong your own custom themes.
          (There's&nbsp;
          %a{ :href => "http://documentup.com/carlo/droplings-default-theme" }> documentation
          \.)

        %p
          The
          %strong maximum file size
          of the files you share is only restricted by the size of your
          Dropbox account.

        %p
          Droplings
          %strong requires
          OS X 10.6 or higher, running on a 64bit
          architecture (i.e. any 2007+ Mac should do).  And of course you
          need a free or Pro
          %a{ :href => "http://db.tt/T84kkEv" } Dropbox account.

        %p
          Droplings is free at the moment as the 0.9.x versions are
          considered betas.  Once we reach 1.0 there'll be a (modest) price
          tag.

        %p#download
          %a{ :href => "http://drpln.gs/QjNR5F" }
            %i.icon-download-alt
            Download Droplings 0.9.4

        %p
          If you want to be informed of what's going on with Droplings,
          %a{ :href => "http://twitter.com/drplings" }
            follow @drplngs on Twitter.
          If you need to contact me, Carlo Zottmann, feel free to send me
          %a{ :href => "mailto:droplings@municode.de" } an email.


        %hr

        %p#imprint
          %strong Impressum/imprint:
          Carlo Zottmann, Zeisigweg 30, 81827 MÃ¼nchen, Germany
          \ &middot; droplings@municode.de
          \ &middot; USt-ID: DE260224054


